15 "ARTICLE 37
16 10-1-960.
17 As used in this article, the term 'HVAC' means heating, ventilation, and air-conditioning.
18 10-1-961.
19 (a) If a residential real property that includes an HVAC system as a fixture to the property
20 is conveyed to a new owner, any manufacturer's warranty in effect on that system or any
21 component of that system:
22 (1) Shall be automatically transferred to the new owner; and
23 (2) Shall continue in effect as if the new owner was the original purchaser of such system
24 or component, as applicable.
25 (b) A manufacturer shall continue to be obligated under the terms of any warranty
26 transferred pursuant to subsection (a) of this Code section and shall not charge a fee for the
27 transfer of such warranty.
28 (c) A transfer of any manufacturer's warranty pursuant to subsection (a) of this Code
29 section shall not extend the remaining term of the warranty.
30 10-1-962.
31 (a) The full term of a manufacturer's, distributor's, or retailer's warranty of an HVAC
32 system or any component of such system shall be effective in this state on the date of
33 installation if installed by a contractor licensed under Chapter 14 of Title 43.
34 (b) If a manufacturer, distributor, or retailer of an HVAC system or any component of such
35 system provides a warranty or product registration card or form, or an electronic, online
36 warranty or product registration form, the card or form shall contain the following
37 information, displayed in a clear and conspicuous manner:
38 (1) The card or form is for registration of the product; and
